<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1322,1751,1857]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The external male genitalia are generalized, but can be differentiated by the gonostylus. The cercus is free, not embedded into tergite 
<number box="[804,819,1791,1817]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="9.0">9</number>
as in 
<taxonomicName box="[893,1004,1791,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Eutolmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[893,1004,1791,1816]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Eutolmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two species of South Korean 
<taxonomicName box="[358,480,1831,1856]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Machimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[358,480,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Machimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily distinguished by their color and seasonality.
</paragraph>
